<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Gello:
[B]I've CH'ed enchanters before during battle.  Never had one die while casting it.  Buffed to the gills they easily break 3k hp.  Even if they have just 2k hp's CH is easily the most efficient heal to use on them.  It just takes some awareness of what's going on, foresight into how well a situation is under control, and of course timing.

The worst clerics imho are the ones that go through their EQ life with no awareness of situation.  [i]All[/i] spells are situational.  If you only heal by rote and never take the circumstances into consideration, you will be an awful cleric.  You'll never be the cleric that can make a group do the impossible.  You'll only be marginally better than a druid but without ports and snare.

That cleric's problem was simple misjudgement and/or bad timing.  Your problem as a cleric is that 'ONLY' word.  Timing and judgement can be refined over time.  Stubborn ignorance of circumstances is not so easy to cure.[/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
